						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Ziggy587 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Thanks for the link. So if I used a 74xx74, could I wire it like this?<br /></div>(No.) The 74'74 will copy the value from the D pin to the Q pin when the CLK pin goes from low to high. So if you tie D high all the time ... Q will always be high.<br /><br /><a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=165239#p165239" class="postlink">This is what you want</a> if you're using a 74'74.</div>

